            <title>[CASSANDRA-7784] DROP table leaves the counter and row cache in a temporarily inconsistent state that, if saved during, will cause an exception to be thrown</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7784</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It looks like this is quite a realistic race to hit reasonably often, since we forceBlockingFlush after removing from Schema.cfIdMap, so there could be a lengthy window to overlap with an auto-save&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12734569">CASSANDRA-7784</key>
            <summary>DROP table leaves the counter and row cache in a temporarily inconsistent state that, if saved during, will cause an exception to be thrown</summary>
