                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14132641" author="benedict" created="Sat, 13 Sep 2014 11:27:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Any news on a patch for this? We should really have got this into 2.1.0, but should definitely fix it for 2.1.1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14135082" author="benedict" created="Tue, 16 Sep 2014 07:22:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Mostly LGTM, in fact it seems like an obvious improvement all round. But I&apos;d either remove the &amp;#64;Deprecated method entirely, or not deprecate it. Since it&apos;s only used in one very cheap to replace place, I&apos;d simply drop it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14135088" author="iamaleksey" created="Tue, 16 Sep 2014 07:27:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If you waited for a few minutes till I marked the issue patch available, I would&apos;ve mentioned that the method will be killed in 3.0, but we need it in 2.1 to load 2.0-created caches.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14135100" author="benedict" created="Tue, 16 Sep 2014 07:38:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah, yes, I see the confusing part is that it hasn&apos;t been replaced in a place where it could have been, but the second usage is a place where it &lt;em&gt;couldn&apos;t&lt;/em&gt; be. It would be clearer if the first usage was replaced, so it were more obvious. Possibly also dropping the UUID from the parameter list. But no biggy&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14135105" author="iamaleksey" created="Tue, 16 Sep 2014 07:41:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually changed the first usage to the uuid-only version on commit already.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3.0 merge removed the deprecated method + the cfId == null special case in DD#getSerializedCachePath() itself.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
